Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically evaluates the performance of BERT on the SQuAD2.0 dataset. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper explores the efficiency of BERT in terms of training time, inference time, and total number of model parameters. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with evaluating the performance of an AI model (BERT) on a specific task. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the SQuAD2.0 dataset involves answering questions based on a given context, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with a neural network model (BERT) and explores its efficiency.
